text.section:
The outcome measurement system shall:
address areas of safety, permanence, and well-being for all children in the State child welfare system;
measure performance at the State and local levels;
expand on federal outcome measures;
use the indicators in §§ 5-1303 through 5-1306 of this subtitle to measure outcomes; and
be used in whole or in part in the Department's annual managing for results submission.
